quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  21,73,"And We made them leaders, guiding by Our command, and We revealed to them<i class=""s"">(the command of) </i>performing good works and establishing the prayer and bringing{1}the purifying charity{2}, for of Us they were worshipers.",footnotes:1:The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.|2:The Arabic word used is zakāt, which denotes purification and growth.
  21,74,"And Lot—We gave him wise judgment and knowledge, and We delivered him from the town that used to practice nasty things. They were indeed a wicked, defiantly disobedient people."
  21,75,"And We entered him into Our mercy; He is{1}indeed one of the righteous.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an speaks about the prophets using present tense; this should be pondered by the reader.
  21,76,"And Noah, when he called before, so We responded to him and delivered him and his family from the great calamity."
  21,77,"And We supported him against the people who disbelieved Our signs; indeed, they were a wicked people, so We drowned them all."
  21,78,"And David and Solomon, when they gave judgment in the case of the field, when some people’s sheep wandered therein by night. And to their judgment We were witnesses."
  21,79,"Yet We made Solomon understand it, and to each We gave wise judgment and knowledge. And We subjected the mountains to give<i class=""s"">(God) </i>due exaltation along with David, and the birds as well—surely We did."
  21,80,"And We taught him the making of shields for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, <span class=""h"">so that they may secure<sup foot_note=""80579"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">you</span>from your violence, so are you then appreciative?"
  21,81,"And to Solomon the stormy <span class=""h"">wind<sup foot_note=""80580"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, blowing at his command towards the land that We had blessed. And We well knew of everything."
